1
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,640
PREVIOUSLY

2
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,840
- Fire!
- Fire!

3
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,240
Somebody, help me!

4
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,720
Berm!

5
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,800
Ms. Kanya told me that you play the bass.

6
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,120
Do you want to join our band?

7
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:35,040
<i>I'm graduating, Petch.</i>

8
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:38,160
<i>No matter how much time passes by,</i>

9
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,800
<i>I still think about you every single day.</i>

10
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:42,840
Petch will be out soon.

11
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:45,520
<i>I'll take our son home.</i>

12
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,160
We will never forget this place,

13
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,640
but we won't be back again.

14
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,720
Wait for me.

15
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,960
Once you're out,
we'll get the band back together.

16
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,480
<i>Are you really leaving this place?</i>

17
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,920
I made a promise to myself.

18
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,640
<i>If I don't succeed,</i>

19
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,360
<i>I won't face my dad ever again.</i>

20
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,360
Come on, dear. Let's talk over there.

21
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:03,440
Right. There's someone waiting for you.

22
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,640
- Dao!
- Dao!

23
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,360
Pin! Prae!

24
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:13,040
I missed you guys so much.

25
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:16,680
Wow, you looked great before,
but you have leveled up!

26
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:20,120
Enough with the flattery.
So have both of you.

27
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,560
- Come this way.
- Come on.

28
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:34,720
<i>Sitting all alone like this</i>
<i>It's actually okay</i>

29
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:39,320
<i>Whatever I do, I'm in a good mood</i>

30
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:45,240
<i>I don't know why</i>
<i>It wasn't like this before</i>

31
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,840
<i>Why is that?</i>

32
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:54,560
<i>Even though in reality</i>
<i>Everything is still the same</i>

33
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:59,480
<i>So what is this new feeling</i>
<i>Added to my heart?</i>

34
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,840
<i>Deep down I know</i>

35
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:07,080
<i>It must mean something</i>

36
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:11,760
<i>And is that answer you?</i>

37
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:18,040
<i>The one who made everything change</i>
<i>Until today feels brand new</i>

38
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,600
<i>You make me think</i>

39
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:25,520
<i>This world is so much brighter…</i>

40
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,320
Are you the real singer?

41
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:32,360
What…

42
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,160
Were you lip-syncing, Ake?

43
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,960
You're good.

44
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,960
It's a thumbs up from me.

45
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,920
Dao, sweetie.

46
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,640
He didn't mean to deceive you or anything.

47
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:51,160
He just wanted to surprise you.

48
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:53,960
Dao.

49
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,360
It's just like what your mom said.

50
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,040
I was acting.

51
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,560
Is that so?

52
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,800
Then…

53
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,920
I like your acting.

54
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:10,960
Pin, Prae, let's get inside.

55
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,240
Okay. We have a lot of catching up to do.

56
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,720
If you're going to keep on lying,

57
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,280
at least make it believable.

58
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,080
Got it.

59
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,120
She's sassy like you.

60
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:35,280
Honey, stop joking about it.

61
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:38,880
Look at Ake. Poor guy.

62
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,040
Dao has got him good.

63
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,240
It's okay, ma'am.

64
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:43,480
I take it as just

65
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,360
playful teasing.

66
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,760
It won't change what I feel about her.

67
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,720
I would take this as a chance
to ask for your permission.

68
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,600
Dam, where are you?

69
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:25,720
I bought a blanket
and other useful stuff for you.

70
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,800
Did you get me something to eat?

71
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,600
Why did you call?

72
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:35,720
I just wanted to try the new phone
you bought for me.

73
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,240
High-quality sound and camera.

74
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,560
Let's see.

75
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,360
Don't just try out the phone.

76
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:47,120
We have housing, electricity, water,
and food bills to worry about.

77
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,840
With my remaining cash,

78
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,120
we won't last longer than a month.

79
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,320
This is the answer.

80
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:58,200
I'll have you create a channel
and become a music creator.

81
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,320
Music creator?

82
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,240
Yes.

83
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:05,120
You don't need a label
to become an artist.

84
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,000
Here.

85
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:10,760
All you have to do is take the new guitar

86
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:13,760
that you bought
with your hard-earned money and play it.

87
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:14,920
Hold it.

88
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,760
I'll record you and we'll upload it.

89
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,280
When we get tons of views,

90
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,480
we'll earn millions.

91
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:24,520
Then, you can show your face
to Mr. Nop again.

92
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,240
Will it be that easy?

93
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:36,080
You'll never know until you try.

94
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:42,520
We'll rehearse today.

95
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,840
Tomorrow,

96
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,160
we'll film it on the rooftop.

97
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,000
That's nice.

98
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,360
- Right?
- Yes.

99
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,960
I'm going to England for my master's.

100
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,480
Are you following me?

101
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:57,000
Yes, of course.

102
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,600
- Come with me.
- Hey, Dao.

103
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:00,280
Did you know

104
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,840
that she only came back because you did?

105
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,600
Are you serious?

106
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:05,160
You guys are so sweet.

107
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,160
Of course.

108
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,280
Did you come back to see me?

109
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,400
If I didn't come back
for a perfect girl like you,

110
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,400
who would I have come back for?

111
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:16,600
That's right. How could you graduate
within three and a half years, Dao?

112
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:19,160
You're also a piano instructor.
You're awesome.

113
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:20,880
You keep praising me.

114
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:24,600
Seems like I have to give you both
a full bag of souvenirs.

115
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,400
She treats us too well.

116
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,120
Excuse me, ladies.

117
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:32,640
Madam told me to tell you
that lunch is ready.

118
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,960
Thanks. Shall we?

119
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:42,040
Here's your favorite, Dao.

120
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:44,360
Thank you.

121
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:47,480
You know how to treat a lady, Ake.

122
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,640
Just a little.

123
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,720
Maybe she'll see my effort

124
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,480
and give in to me.

125
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,240
Isn't that too much, Ake?

126
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,960
Well, sir…

127
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:00,960
I didn't mean it like that.

128
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,880
I meant,

129
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:06,400
maybe she would agree
to come work with me.

130
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,680
- I see.
- Dao.

131
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,400
Aren't you looking for a job?

132
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:14,160
Would you like to work for me?

133
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,360
That sounds nice.

134
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:19,560
She just graduated in business management.

135
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,840
She could be a great help, Ake.

136
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,080
I don't want to get a job
through connections.

137
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:28,400
I want to get it through my ability.

138
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,200
Dao.

139
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,440
It won't just be handed to you.

140
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,960
You have to use your skills
to go through interviews

141
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:39,040
and a probation period
just like everyone else.

142
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:40,120
I see.

143
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,880
That sounds even better.

144
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:45,320
Righteous and fair.
Just like what you're looking for, Dao.

145
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,520
But…

146
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:50,600
Just give it a try.

147
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:52,840
If you pass the interview,
you can decide later.

148
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,280
Okay, sweetie?

149
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,920
Okay, Mom.

150
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:00,160
Eat up, dear.

151
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:08,120
Five, four, three, two, one, action.

152
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,800
Hi. I'm Petch.

153
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:15,280
Today, I'm singing in the first epic-sode.

154
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,720
Hold up. Wait.

155
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:19,080
Episode, not epic-sode.

156
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,080
What is it?

157
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,160
Episode.

158
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:23,400
- Episode?
- Right. Let's do it again.

159
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,160
I'm Petch.

160
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,800
Today, I'm going to sing…

161
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:33,280
in the first episode, so…

162
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:36,080
I hope everyone enjoys…

163
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:38,040
our channel…

164
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,720
Petch and Damrong.

165
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,160
Man.

166
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:44,080
What's wrong with you?
You were fine during the rehearsal.

167
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:45,120
What is it?

168
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,760
I don't know.
I'm afraid of failing perhaps?

169
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:52,040
I have to speak to the camera.

170
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,600
It's different from a crowd.

171
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,400
Imagine. Imagine it.

172
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,640
Use your imagination, you know?

173
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,400
Imagination.

174
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,360
It won't work.

175
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:12,240
Let's look for on-site gigs.

176
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,360
- Bummer.
- Let's go.

177
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:17,000
Master Petch, don't give up just yet.

178
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,440
Don't give up.

179
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:20,760
Come on.

180
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:26,320
I can't do it. What do you want me to do?

181
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:28,480
Calm down, man.

182
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:32,080
Sit down. Sit here.

183
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,000
Come on.

184
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,040
Come on. There.

185
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:39,880
Calm down. I'll get you some fresh water.
Wait here.

186
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:40,920
Don't force it, Dam.

187
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,840
Believe me.

188
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,280
This is going to work.

189
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:07,640
Ake.

190
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,480
This is not the way to the company.

191
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,320
Dao.

192
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,880
I'm not going to murder you somewhere.

193
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:18,160
Ake, I'm out with you for a job interview.

194
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:21,360
Interviews don't strictly have
to be held at the office, do they?

195
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:24,360
Where do you want me
to attend the interview?

196
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,080
When we arrive,

197
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:28,920
you'll find out.

198
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:55,320
Did Dam go to Chao Phraya
for a bottle of water?

199
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,760
Why is he not here yet?

200
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:05,720
DAM: SENT A PHOTO

201
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:17,440
How do you feel about that, Petch?

202
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:20,880
Does seeing Dao's picture
make you feel hydrated?

203
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,760
Where did you get it from?

204
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:25,640
That?

205
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,720
She posted it on her social account,

206
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,560
so I sent it to you.

207
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,040
What for, dude?

208
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,520
Don't you miss Dao?

209
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,040
It's none of your business.

210
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:38,600
Oh, please. Petch.

211
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,200
You can lie to anyone.

212
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,560
But can you really

213
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:46,640
lie to yourself?

214
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,360
Stop being so dramatic.

215
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:53,120
I don't see how Dao
has anything to do with this.

216
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,760
Is that so? I see it, though.

217
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,120
A moment, please.

218
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:14,560
Now, you have Natedao
to accompany you here.

219
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,200
Here.

220
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:19,520
Dao will be here listening to your songs

221
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:22,440
and whatever you have to say.

222
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:24,960
You can do it in one take now, right?

223
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:28,600
Dam, my man.

224
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,280
They said

225
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:37,160
good songs with meaningful lyrics

226
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:40,680
have someone living in them.

227
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,200
Let's listen and see

228
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:48,320
who pops up in your mind.

229
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:07,480
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

230
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:13,560
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

231
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:20,560
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

232
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:25,360
<i>But never reaching you</i>

233
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:31,480
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

234
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:37,960
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

235
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:44,400
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

236
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:50,560
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

237
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:55,920
<i>You are out of reach</i>

238
00:16:56,440 --> 00:17:02,120
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

239
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:07,720
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

240
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:13,400
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

241
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:19,720
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

242
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:25,640
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

243
00:17:26,599 --> 00:17:32,480
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

244
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:38,600
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

245
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:31,320
Dao.

246
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:34,120
Dao, hey. Dao.

247
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:37,040
Where are you going, honey?

248
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,080
Ake.

249
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,880
I've wasted enough time. I'm leaving.

250
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:43,240
Dao.

251
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:45,640
Please relax once in a while.

252
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:49,920
I prepared for an interview,
not for an amusement park.

253
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,680
This is it, Dao.

254
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:55,280
This is your work trial.

255
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,120
I don't understand. What job is this?

256
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:00,120
It's…

257
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:03,200
accompanying and comforting me.

258
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:05,480
What?

259
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,800
It's an easy job, Dao.

260
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:12,600
Your tasks include going out,
eating out, and shopping with me.

261
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:15,120
Have you lost your mind?

262
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,960
Dao.

263
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:19,720
Hey, Dao.

264
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:22,360
Why are you being harsh on me
all of a sudden?

265
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:23,680
Don't you realize it?

266
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,520
You're that type of man
who looks down on women,

267
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,440
hence this job.

268
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:29,920
Dao.

269
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,800
I haven't thought of that at all.

270
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,720
Then please think for once.

271
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:35,480
In this day and age,

272
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:37,960
men do not rule the world anymore.

273
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,000
You're so hard to please.

274
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:57,240
Hello, sir.

275
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:58,400
Dao.

276
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:02,080
I just called your father
a little while ago.

277
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:05,160
Do you have time to stop by my office?

278
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,480
I would like to talk.

279
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:08,800
Of course. I'm on my way.

280
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:19,760
Did Ake hire you to hang out with him?

281
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:23,000
How could he do that? What a wack.

282
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:26,040
You know the word "wack"?

283
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,160
Just a little.

284
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:30,880
My customers are young,
so I need to keep up with the times.

285
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,560
That's nice.

286
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:35,160
I wish for more people like you
in society.

287
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:39,880
I also wish for more young people
like you in my company.

288
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:43,160
Hey.

289
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,800
I really mean it.

290
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:49,040
I want you to work for my company.

291
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,240
Thank you for your kindness.

292
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:55,600
It's not about being kind, Dao.

293
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:58,920
I read through your education profile.

294
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:04,200
I see your potential, musical knowledge,
and knack for business.

295
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,360
You're the right fit for my company.

296
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:09,560
Do you really mean it?

297
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:14,840
Dao.

298
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:18,160
How did you get here?

299
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:23,440
Mr. Sompob called me
and offered me a job here.

300
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:25,680
Really, Uncle?

301
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:28,880
What position did you offer her?

302
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:30,960
I offered her your position.

303
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,720
I was joking. Why were you startled?

304
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,960
Uncle, please don't fool around like this.

305
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:41,280
I was lost for a second.

306
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,640
Okay, how about

307
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:48,800
I assign you to learn about our network,

308
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:54,240
starting from working at Ake's pub
as an executive director for six months,

309
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,720
then returning to the headquarters?

310
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:58,640
Is that okay with you?

311
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:02,400
Yes. I'll do my best.

312
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,280
Thank you for the opportunity.

313
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:13,320
Business has been slow lately.

314
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,480
Come back some other time.

315
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:16,560
It's all right, sir.

316
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:20,440
If you need more people, please call me.

317
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:22,680
Okay. I'll get back to work now.

318
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:24,240
- Thank you, sir.
- All right.

319
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:40,160
Why is it like this? This is so tiring.

320
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:42,200
- What's wrong, Dam?
- Hey, Petch.

321
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:45,000
It's our video.

322
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,920
It has been over a month,

323
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,080
but look at the view count.

324
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,240
Only a few hundred?

325
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:50,880
How could I not be down?

326
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,960
If we don't keep going, we will lose.

327
00:22:57,480 --> 00:22:59,000
We need to do more research.

328
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,640
Oh, Petch.

329
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:03,280
What else could you have done?

330
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:05,360
You sang the song so beautifully.

331
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,120
Why is no one watching?

332
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:08,920
Don't blame the viewers.

333
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,640
If we don't blame them,
then who should be blamed?

334
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,320
We earn from views.

335
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:15,640
More views mean more money.

336
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:22,440
What's with the long face?

337
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:25,560
Didn't get a job, did you?

338
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:30,160
He wouldn't hire me.

339
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:38,240
How are we going to pay rent?

340
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:39,360
It's due today.

341
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,880
This is my last one.

342
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:55,800
Go buy eggs, rice,
and top up the Internet.

343
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,920
What about you?

344
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,120
You're not coming?

345
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:02,560
No.

346
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:07,800
I'll talk to the landlord
and ask for an extension.

347
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,920
Okay. Right.

348
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,720
Top up the Internet.

349
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:16,920
See you.

350
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:29,280
- How much?
- Forty baht.

351
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:33,960
Forty baht.

352
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,240
Here.

353
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:40,840
Where are you going, baby?

354
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:42,880
Wet trash.

355
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,160
I know I'm pretty.

356
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:47,480
I don't need you
hitting on me to prove it.

357
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,160
You!

358
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:54,160
You bastards even took my purse!

359
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,800
Stop it, you thieves.

360
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,680
Hey, you!

361
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:04,360
Hey.

362
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:05,680
It hurts.

363
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:07,040
Hey.

364
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,960
Take this.

365
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,840
How does it feel? You know me now?

366
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:17,480
- You bitch.
- Try me.

367
00:25:17,560 --> 00:25:19,160
I'll teach you a lesson.

368
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:22,480
There you go.

369
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:23,400
That hurts.

370
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:25,160
Get up now.

371
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:30,080
Hey! Don't hurt women.

372
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:38,920
- Gosh! It hurts. Oh, it hurts so bad!
- What's wrong with her?

373
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,160
Why are you meddling?

374
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:47,720
So cool, brother.

375
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,480
Hey, stop!

376
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:54,320
Gosh! It hurts. It really does!

377
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:55,680
It hurts so bad!

378
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:57,480
- Gosh!
- Hey.

379
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:58,440
Are you all right?

380
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:02,400
Oh, it hurts. It really hurts!

381
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:03,960
Your arm or your leg?

382
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:07,720
Not my arm, not my leg.

383
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:09,480
But…

384
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:13,600
<i>It hurts to love you</i>
<i>But I can't let you know</i>

385
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:19,080
<i>It hurts to keep it just to myself</i>

386
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:25,560
Oh, you. Can't you read the room?

387
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,960
Don't laugh. I'm being serious.

388
00:26:28,040 --> 00:26:29,360
You're funny.

389
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:33,920
Are you from out of town?

390
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:35,160
Why!

391
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:38,600
I dress exactly like celebrities.

392
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,960
How do you know I'm from out of town?

393
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:43,920
I guess you're not in pain, then.

394
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,960
Oh, gosh! It hurts!

395
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:48,800
It hurts.

396
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:52,120
I was just acting tough.

397
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:54,560
My legs are quite hurt.

398
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:57,440
Here and here too.

399
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:58,600
It hurts!

400
00:26:59,120 --> 00:27:01,040
Brother, can you drop me off?

401
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:02,240
Where do you live?

402
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:04,280
The dorm at the end of this alley.

403
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:08,440
Can you carry me there, please?

404
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:10,520
I'm too hurt. I can't walk.

405
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:13,960
Please?

406
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:15,080
Please? Pretty please?

407
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,600
My legs are hurting.

408
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:19,120
It hurts.

409
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:21,080
Please. Pretty please?

410
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:24,480
All right.

411
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,960
Let's get you ready before I carry you.

412
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:29,120
Stand up first.

413
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:35,560
Please close your eyes.

414
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:38,280
I will count to three,
then you can open them.

415
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:39,840
Now?

416
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:40,840
Yes.

417
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,640
One.

418
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:53,400
Two.

419
00:27:55,320 --> 00:27:56,160
Three.

420
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:01,480
You are the naughty type, aren't you?

421
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:07,680
It feels so romantic.

422
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:12,000
I'm so happy.

423
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:14,880
I feel like we're in the series I watched.

424
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:18,160
A man carries the girl under the sunset.

425
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:19,880
It's so romantic!

426
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:24,080
Are you okay, brother?

427
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,000
Oh, right.

428
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:30,120
Your sweetness hurts my eyes, Sai Kaew.

429
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:32,240
Oh, I see.

430
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:36,360
But I have to say.
Your voice sounds familiar.

431
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,200
You sound like my brother, Dammy.

432
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:43,200
I don't feel well today.

433
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:45,640
Oh, I see.

434
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:49,480
I think you are handsome and good.

435
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:52,320
You're not like Dammy
who has a potty mouth and is ugly.

436
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:55,960
Hey!

437
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,000
It hurts!

438
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:58,520
Dammy!

439
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:00,520
- It's you?
- It's me.

440
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:03,400
I carried you from there
and now, we're here.

441
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:04,440
You're on your own now!

442
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:05,880
Why? Can't you carry me?

443
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:07,080
That's enough.

444
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,760
You guys are siblings, aren't you?

445
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:11,400
Why do you fight so much?

446
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:12,320
What?

447
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:16,360
Do you know this Dammy, handsome brother?

448
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,680
Of course, silly.

449
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,680
- Petch and I
- What?

450
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,240
are close friends.

451
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,160
I see.

452
00:29:23,800 --> 00:29:25,000
It's you, Petch?

453
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:29,520
Although you tricked me with this Dammy,

454
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:31,160
I don't really mind.

455
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:33,240
Handsome men do nothing wrong.

456
00:29:33,320 --> 00:29:35,080
I forgive you, Petch.

457
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,920
- Hey.
- What's wrong?

458
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,360
Are you all right, my man?

459
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:42,400
- What's wrong?
- I'm throwing up!

460
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:44,840
Dammy, you always act stupid.

461
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,560
All right, that's enough.

462
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:49,880
Why are you doing this in the sun?

463
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:51,880
Let's get inside.

464
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,000
Okay.

465
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:55,440
- Come on. Let's go.
- Go.

466
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:56,440
Go on.

467
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:58,320
Look at her.

468
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,440
Look at her! Carry your own bag! Walk!

469
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:01,680
Hey! Shut up!

470
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,800
Hey.

471
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:09,760
Take that!

472
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:13,040
- Hey, Joke.
- What?

473
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:14,880
Help me carry the drinks.

474
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:16,960
There are plenty of VIP orders today.

475
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:18,760
Hey.

476
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:21,280
Know your place.

477
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:23,720
What right do you have to boss me around?

478
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:25,800
There are not enough staff here.

479
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:27,120
Please help out.

480
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,040
Hey.

481
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:30,680
I lost the game.

482
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,160
I lost!

483
00:30:32,240 --> 00:30:33,240
Hey.

484
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,200
Listen to me carefully.

485
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:38,600
I am not helping.

486
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:41,000
Are you my boss?

487
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:43,200
No, you're not!

488
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:44,760
Don't tell me what to do.

489
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:46,240
Go away!

490
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:48,880
Who told you to ruin my mood
while I was playing games?

491
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:51,000
I will fire all of you! Don't work here.

492
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,720
Leave! Go on.

493
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:55,320
Why you… You're getting on my nerves!

494
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:57,920
Oh, these guys.

495
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,280
I swear… Oh!

496
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:01,240
Oh, dear.

497
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:02,680
It's Ms. Dao.

498
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:06,800
Ms. Dao, hello.

499
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:08,920
Is there anything I can help you with?

500
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,720
Please tell me.

501
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:14,320
I can do anything from A to Z.

502
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:17,160
What is your job?

503
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:18,200
Well…

504
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:20,280
I'm the head waiter.

505
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:24,440
Being the head
is to be the example for others,

506
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:27,280
not playing games
and leaving your job for others to do.

507
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,320
Gosh.

508
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:32,200
- It hurts.
- What's wrong?

509
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:36,200
Your words hurt me.

510
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:38,760
- Joke.
- Yes, Ms. Dao.

511
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:40,840
I didn't call you out in front of everyone

512
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:43,880
because I didn't want to humiliate you.

513
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:48,320
You should improve yourself,
so we can work together for a long time.

514
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:50,440
Yes, Ms. Dao.

515
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:52,960
I'll improve myself.

516
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:57,320
That's good. I like hardworking staff
and dislike brownnosers.

517
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:00,680
This way, ma'am.

518
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:04,280
Well.

519
00:32:05,280 --> 00:32:08,720
I'm flattered.
She called me out, but I like it.

520
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:11,840
I got your address from Aunty Noi,

521
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:14,520
so I'm moving in with you.

522
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:17,960
- Stand up!
- No.

523
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,440
Go back to Aunty Noi's.

524
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:22,480
There's nothing to do in Takhli.

525
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:24,720
Let me stay here with you, Dam.

526
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:26,200
I can look for a job here.

527
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:28,360
I told you that you can't!

528
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,000
Can't you see this tiny room?

529
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:32,440
Petch and I are suffering enough.

530
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:35,280
If you move in here,
we'll be squeezed to death.

531
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,800
Hey. You don't know that.
What if you let me stay?

532
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:39,320
I might be of great help.

533
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:44,080
A great help?
A great burden, probably. Leave now.

534
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:47,640
No! Petch, please help me talk to him.

535
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:50,600
I don't want to go back to Takhli.

536
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,560
Listen to Dam.

537
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,880
The cost of living in Bangkok
is expensive.

538
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:05,160
You'll be better in the countryside.

539
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:10,360
I will see you off at the bus stop.

540
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:12,920
No. I'm not leaving.
I'll be with Petch here.

541
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:14,200
No.

542
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:17,080
No, you say? No? Leave now.

543
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:18,280
No, I'm not leaving.

544
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:19,840
Sai! Leave now!

545
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:21,080
Leave.

546
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,080
I don't want to go home.

547
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:43,960
Dam, are you back already?

548
00:33:49,480 --> 00:33:51,920
It's the end of the month.
Pay the rent now.

549
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:54,000
Can I pay you next month, please?

550
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:56,920
I'm a man of my word.

551
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:58,720
If you can't pay now, you can't stay!

552
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:00,720
Ped, Gai, kick them out.

553
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,040
Take everything out.

554
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:05,200
- Hey.
- Get out.

555
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:07,640
- Take this.
- Wait.

556
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,719
- Take them out.
- What are you doing?

557
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:12,760
Dam, calm down!

558
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:13,920
Don't get mad.

559
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:15,360
Why are they touching our stuff?

560
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:19,400
Turn around.
She's here for the rent payment.

561
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:23,600
Pay me then, young boy.

562
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,639
Is 5,000 enough, petty aunty?

563
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:37,440
Petty is still better
than pouting, poor sugar baby.

564
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:40,239
Thank you for this. Ped, Gai, let's go.

565
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:50,560
What's up now, debtors?

566
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:53,080
Can I stay here now?

567
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:58,240
Okay.

568
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:00,680
- As you wish.
- Yes!

569
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:03,400
I get to live here now. I'm so happy.

570
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:07,600
Help me pick those.

571
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,160
Dao.

572
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:17,280
This report is quite well done.

573
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:19,360
I chose the right person for the job.

574
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:22,800
I'm not that great, sir. I'm new here.

575
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:24,480
I have so many things to learn.

576
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:30,640
Seriously, Dao.

577
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:35,920
You reduced the cost in half,
which Ake could never do.

578
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:39,600
He has taught me a lot.

579
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:40,520
Right.

580
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:42,840
Don't put in a good word for him.

581
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:45,280
I know very well how he is.

582
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:46,680
Look around.

583
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:48,480
I'm here for the reports

584
00:35:48,560 --> 00:35:50,000
and he's nowhere to be found.

585
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:52,040
I don't know where he has gone.

586
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:09,360
- Ake, sir.
- Hey!

587
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:11,640
Mud, why are you here?

588
00:36:12,600 --> 00:36:14,520
I didn't mean to interrupt.

589
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:17,760
The director is checking
the reports from the pub.

590
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:20,080
He has been looking for you.

591
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:21,680
My uncle is here?

592
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:23,640
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

593
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:25,680
You turned off your phone, sir.

594
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:27,880
Damn.

595
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:28,920
Let's go now.

596
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:35,480
If there is nothing else,

597
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:37,600
I would excuse myself
to other tasks downstairs.

598
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:39,040
Okay.

599
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:47,880
Uncle.

600
00:36:48,400 --> 00:36:49,680
I'm sorry.

601
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:52,520
I was with the external client
and it took a while to leave.

602
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:56,720
Dao.

603
00:36:57,240 --> 00:36:58,960
Won't you stay for the meeting?

604
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:03,000
My part of the responsibilities
has been taken care of.

605
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:04,640
Please excuse me.

606
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,040
Uncle.

607
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:22,000
Did Dao

608
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:23,880
say anything about me?

609
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:26,960
Natedao is a real aristocrat.

610
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:30,000
She is not trash like you.

611
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:34,160
You never

612
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:36,600
see me as a decent person.

613
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:38,840
There is one decent choice

614
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:41,880
you have made.

615
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:45,720
Natedao is the perfect life partner.

616
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:49,800
So does that mean

617
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:52,000
if I marry Natedao,

618
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:54,600
you will approve of it?

619
00:37:59,200 --> 00:38:00,720
I will definitely approve.

620
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:03,000
Under the condition

621
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:06,600
that you are both willing participants

622
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:09,160
and neither is coerced.

623
00:38:10,160 --> 00:38:13,120
If Natedao loves you
and wants to marry you,

624
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:16,600
I will fully support it.

625
00:38:20,960 --> 00:38:22,360
Thank you, Uncle.

626
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:26,680
I'll hurry and make her like me back.

627
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:30,800
Please ask her parents' permission for me.

628
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:45,240
Oh, hey.

629
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:49,200
Petch and I will sleep here
and you, Sai, on the other side.

630
00:38:55,280 --> 00:38:56,320
Hey.

631
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:59,160
Speak to your creditor more nicely, Dammy.

632
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:01,440
You…

633
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:06,080
Five thousand baht and you act
like a madam. Wait for my turn.

634
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:09,320
I will send you back to Takhli!

635
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:12,200
Hey, stop fighting.

636
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:15,200
There are only two pillows, Sai.

637
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,120
Here.

638
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,600
Take mine.

639
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:21,760
I will sleep on my towel tonight.

640
00:39:24,120 --> 00:39:26,040
What a warm brother.

641
00:39:27,160 --> 00:39:30,560
You can take your pillow, Petch.

642
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:33,640
I can sleep on your chest.

643
00:39:33,720 --> 00:39:36,840
- It would warm my heart so much.
- "It would warm my heart so much."

644
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,880
Cut it out.

645
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:41,320
Knock it off!

646
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:44,280
What's wrong with you, Dammy?

647
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:47,320
My friend is not food.
Stop drooling over him.

648
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,880
I was just flirting…

649
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:53,240
I mean, I was fooling around
to brighten up the mood.

650
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:54,680
Right, Petch?

651
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:57,920
That's nice.

652
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:00,040
But rather than fooling around,

653
00:40:00,120 --> 00:40:03,280
I think we should all just start
looking for a job.

654
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:09,080
Petch called your nonsense.

655
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:11,880
I know! Don't say it again.

656
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:17,040
Don't worry, Petch.

657
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:20,000
You'll have a job by the end of this week.

658
00:40:42,560 --> 00:40:43,760
AIR-CONDITIONED BUS, 10 BAHT

659
00:40:49,720 --> 00:40:54,040
FIRST TIME ON A BUS

660
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:00,280
Petch.

661
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:03,640
Where were you all this time?

662
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:22,080
Where were you, Sai?

663
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:24,200
Why did you leave your dirty dish?

664
00:41:24,280 --> 00:41:27,920
Would it kill you to wash it?

665
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,760
Hey.

666
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:33,480
- Come here.
- I can fight you too.

667
00:41:34,080 --> 00:41:35,920
- Hey.
- Hey!

668
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:41,040
Are you fighting again?

669
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:44,040
Can't you just talk?

670
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:46,120
Listen to her, Petch.

671
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:49,360
Her future husband is cursed for life.

672
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:53,880
You too, Dammy. You'll never be married.

673
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:56,880
You're always nagging.
No one will take you.

674
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:00,960
- You!
- Petch, please help me.

675
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:02,320
Okay, that's enough.

676
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:04,320
Can you please stop fighting?

677
00:42:04,400 --> 00:42:06,440
I've been out all morning
looking for a job.

678
00:42:06,520 --> 00:42:09,600
Don't make me come home
and watch you fight, please.

679
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:18,560
Everyone, listen here.

680
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:22,000
I scored jobs for the two of you.

681
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:24,920
Are you serious?

682
00:42:27,080 --> 00:42:30,480
Here, look here.

683
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:32,120
What is this?

684
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,160
What is it?

685
00:42:34,240 --> 00:42:37,720
The hand of a professional.

686
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:41,400
I'm telling you.

687
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:44,640
I used my charisma to charm an old man.

688
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:46,520
You two can start tomorrow.

689
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,440
What job?

690
00:43:07,160 --> 00:43:10,080
There you are.

691
00:43:10,160 --> 00:43:12,000
Oh, wow.

692
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:14,840
You look so cool, Petch.

693
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:16,560
Even in this uniform,
you look really great.

694
00:43:17,400 --> 00:43:18,240
Hold on.

695
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:22,520
Let me upload this to my SNS.

696
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:24,120
Smile.

697
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:26,760
- Look here.
- I hope your memory card is full.

698
00:43:28,800 --> 00:43:30,640
- There you go!
- Ouch!

699
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:32,680
Why did you hit me, Dammy!

700
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:34,920
You're such a dutty!

701
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:38,080
Dutty? What is it?

702
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:41,200
Dumb and slutty. Dutty!

703
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:43,400
- Are you cursing at me?
- And what?

704
00:43:43,480 --> 00:43:45,480
- It hurts.
- Here!

705
00:43:45,560 --> 00:43:46,600
Enough, both of you.

706
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:48,320
Knock it off.

707
00:43:49,040 --> 00:43:51,040
Let's clean the restroom at the back.

708
00:43:52,320 --> 00:43:54,640
Petch, you're so hardworking.

709
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:56,400
Please be a little lazy.

710
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:58,040
We're paid the same amount of money.

711
00:43:59,080 --> 00:44:00,000
Sai.

712
00:44:00,080 --> 00:44:02,600
You're looking down on yourself
by saying that.

713
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:05,800
Ms. Kanya taught us
back in the Juvenile Training--

714
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:07,040
Stop!

715
00:44:08,080 --> 00:44:09,720
I told you not to mention it.

716
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:15,400
You can't tell anyone
that you and Dam have criminal records.

717
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:18,800
What do you mean?

718
00:44:20,360 --> 00:44:21,960
I got this job

719
00:44:22,040 --> 00:44:24,440
- and the owner didn't know I was--
- Stop!

720
00:44:28,520 --> 00:44:30,880
Be quiet. I told you to zip it.

721
00:44:31,480 --> 00:44:32,760
Hey.

722
00:44:32,840 --> 00:44:37,200
No one knows that you and Dam
were in the training center.

723
00:44:37,920 --> 00:44:38,840
Hey.

724
00:44:39,680 --> 00:44:41,080
If you want me to lie,

725
00:44:41,680 --> 00:44:42,720
I'd rather leave.

726
00:44:42,800 --> 00:44:46,360
- You can't.
- Petch, wait!

727
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:50,000
Are you out of your mind?
Jobs are hard to find.

728
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:53,320
It's true. Please think about it.

729
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:57,880
Truth never dies,
but we are starving to death.

730
00:44:57,960 --> 00:45:00,440
Sai, if you want me to lie,

731
00:45:01,040 --> 00:45:02,160
I can't do it.

732
00:45:02,240 --> 00:45:03,400
Damn, Petch.

733
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:05,560
Sai and I didn't ask you to lie.

734
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:09,560
But if no one asks, then you don't need
to tell anyone, do you?

735
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:10,520
Dam.

736
00:45:11,040 --> 00:45:12,760
You agree with Sai Kaew on this?

737
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:15,480
Petch, is your dream to be a singer?

738
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:18,880
If yes, aren't you supposed to do
your best today?

739
00:45:19,480 --> 00:45:21,080
Dammy finally got something right.

740
00:45:21,680 --> 00:45:24,440
Petch, I'm begging you.

741
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:28,280
Please keep it to yourself
for a month or two,

742
00:45:28,360 --> 00:45:30,600
just until we earn enough to survive.

743
00:45:31,120 --> 00:45:32,240
Please, brother.

744
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:35,280
Hey!

745
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:38,080
You three are chatting again.

746
00:45:38,160 --> 00:45:39,480
Don't you have work to do?

747
00:46:03,120 --> 00:46:04,880
- Go.
- Let's go.

748
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:07,240
- I got the bucket.
- Hurry.

749
00:46:07,320 --> 00:46:08,680
- Yes, sir.
- Yes.

750
00:46:08,760 --> 00:46:13,200
DON'T SMOKE IN THE GAS STATION AREA

751
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:23,360
Mr. Nop.

752
00:46:27,480 --> 00:46:28,400
Mr. Nop.

753
00:46:31,040 --> 00:46:31,880
Dao.

754
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:33,680
Is that you, Dao?

755
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:34,600
Yes, sir.

756
00:46:46,760 --> 00:46:47,920
Hello, sir.

757
00:46:48,000 --> 00:46:49,520
It has been several years.

758
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:51,720
I'm glad that you still recognize me.

759
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:52,960
Of course I do.

760
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:55,560
You're important to my son.

761
00:47:06,520 --> 00:47:07,920
Have some water, Dao.

762
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,520
Thank you, sir.

763
00:47:10,880 --> 00:47:12,480
I still remember it well.

764
00:47:13,280 --> 00:47:16,560
The day you came here
to give me a prize money

765
00:47:17,360 --> 00:47:19,160
and Petch got angry with you.

766
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:22,600
It's just funny when I think about it now.

767
00:47:23,120 --> 00:47:24,680
He was so stubborn.

768
00:47:26,560 --> 00:47:28,720
Petch is that kind of person.

769
00:47:29,920 --> 00:47:31,440
Four years have passed,

770
00:47:31,960 --> 00:47:33,920
but it feels like yesterday.

771
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:38,440
Time passes quickly when you're occupied.

772
00:47:39,680 --> 00:47:43,320
I keep looking for things to do
to keep myself busy,

773
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:45,160
so I don't overthink

774
00:47:45,920 --> 00:47:47,520
and miss Petch that much.

775
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:51,880
Have you met with Petch at all?

776
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:53,720
Have you heard from him?

777
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:57,560
Is Petch not here?

778
00:47:59,800 --> 00:48:01,600
You didn't hear from him?

779
00:48:04,640 --> 00:48:07,000
The last time I was here,

780
00:48:07,080 --> 00:48:10,400
I was about to leave for the States
and now I've just gotten back.

781
00:48:15,040 --> 00:48:17,240
Why? What's going on?

782
00:48:17,800 --> 00:48:18,960
What happened to Petch?

783
00:48:23,520 --> 00:48:24,960
Petch was arrested

784
00:48:25,760 --> 00:48:27,520
for murder.

785
00:48:34,440 --> 00:48:38,960
The judge sent Petch to the Juvenile
Training Center for five years.

786
00:48:40,120 --> 00:48:43,800
But with his good behavior,
he got out early.

787
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:46,840
He just got out earlier this month.

788
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:50,240
I went to pick him up
at the training center

789
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:52,160
and met his teacher there.

790
00:48:52,840 --> 00:48:54,480
She told me he had already left.

791
00:48:56,280 --> 00:48:57,600
When I got home,

792
00:48:58,640 --> 00:49:00,280
all I saw was the letter he left me.

793
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:04,520
He said that if he didn't succeed,

794
00:49:05,680 --> 00:49:07,400
he wouldn't come back home.

795
00:49:08,560 --> 00:49:10,920
I haven't heard from him since.

796
00:49:12,360 --> 00:49:14,040
If you don't succeed,

797
00:49:14,840 --> 00:49:16,600
you won't face anyone,

798
00:49:17,320 --> 00:49:18,760
including me.

799
00:49:39,520 --> 00:49:40,720
Fill it up, please.

800
00:49:49,520 --> 00:49:50,360
Petch.

801
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:55,440
There's no way you can make me
get engaged to Ake.

802
00:49:55,520 --> 00:49:57,440
I've sacrificed everything
for your happiness.

803
00:49:57,520 --> 00:49:59,680
Let me live my life.

804
00:49:59,760 --> 00:50:00,720
- Ma'am?
- Pen!

805
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:03,280
You can run away from everything.

806
00:50:04,880 --> 00:50:07,760
But you can't run away from your heart.

807
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:11,320
Dao, give him your hand.

808
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:13,080
NEXT EPISODE

809
00:50:13,160 --> 00:50:14,720
<i>Dao and Ake?</i>

810
00:50:14,800 --> 00:50:16,960
The engagement party.

811
00:50:17,040 --> 00:50:19,720
Fine quality. Classy.

812
00:50:20,240 --> 00:50:21,080
Petch.

813
00:50:34,440 --> 00:50:39,560
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

814
00:50:40,680 --> 00:50:45,680
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

815
00:50:46,560 --> 00:50:52,520
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

816
00:50:52,600 --> 00:50:57,160
<i>But never reaching you</i>

817
00:50:58,480 --> 00:51:03,320
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

818
00:51:04,680 --> 00:51:09,320
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

819
00:51:10,840 --> 00:51:15,880
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

820
00:51:16,960 --> 00:51:22,360
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

821
00:51:23,440 --> 00:51:27,920
<i>You are out of reach</i>

822
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:34,000
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

823
00:51:35,720 --> 00:51:40,400
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

824
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:45,760
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

825
00:51:46,640 --> 00:51:51,080
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

826
00:51:52,680 --> 00:51:58,520
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

827
00:51:58,600 --> 00:52:04,440
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

828
00:52:04,520 --> 00:52:10,400
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

829
00:52:10,480 --> 00:52:12,040
Subtitle translation by: Natnaree W.
